28/01/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- Foreign Minister Kastriot Islami met on Tuesday (27 January) with the head of the OSCE Presence in Albania, Osmo Lipponen, to discuss bilateral ties and co-operation in reforms.
Islami expressed gratitude for the support provided by the OSCE Presence, particularly its assistance in drafting the land property and restitution bill, electoral reforms and the restructuring of public administration.
In other news, Italy pledged to assist Albania in its efforts to fight corruption and organised crime.
The offer came Tuesday in a meeting between Albanian Prime Minister Fatos Nano and Italian Anti-Mafia Office Deputy Prosecutor Francesco Mandoi.
(Albanian Daily News - 28/01/04;
ATA - 27/01/04)
